      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "udf_ValidUploadFileType",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This specific function is designed to determine whether a given file type is valid for upload, based on predefined criteria."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this function is low. Scalar functions involve straightforward logic, such as simple condition checks or calculations, and this function is expected to perform a basic validation task."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function takes a single input parameter:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@FileType NVARCHAR(50)",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter represents the file type of the file being evaluated. It is expected to be a string that specifies the file extension or MIME type."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Return Type"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The return type of the function is "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "BIT",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". This shows that the function returns a boolean value, where "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " represents a valid file type and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "0",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " represents an invalid file type."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The business logic of the function involves checking the input file type against a predefined list of valid file types. The workflow is as follows:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The function receives the file type as input."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It compares this file type against a list of acceptable file types, which be hardcoded within the function or retrieved from a configuration table."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "If the file type matches one of the valid types, the function returns "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "1",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "If the file type does not match any valid types, the function returns "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "0",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can introduce performance overhead when used in large queries, especially if they are called repeatedly for each row in a result set. This is because scalar functions are executed row-by-row, which can lead to slower performance compared to set-based operations. However, given the simplicity of this function, the performance impact is minimal unless used extensively in large datasets."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Hardcoded Values",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": If the list of valid file types is hardcoded within the function, it can lead to maintenance challenges. Any change in the list requires modifying the function code."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Performance Overhead",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": As with any scalar function, there is a risk of performance degradation if the function is used in queries that process large volumes of data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Limited Flexibility",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The function's logic is fixed, meaning any changes to the validation criteria require code changes. This can be mitigated by externalizing the list of valid file types to a configuration table."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Security Concerns",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": If the function is used to validate file uploads, it is crucial to ensure that the validation logic is comprehensive to prevent security vulnerabilities, such as allowing malicious file types."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "8. Function Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CREATE FUNCTION [Rules].[udf_ValidUploadFileType](@col sql_variant) RETURNS bit AS begin return case when @col IN ('OR','AD','DD','XX','VA','MD') then 1 else 0 end   end;```\n"
        }
      ]
    }
